Shazam, one of the world’s most popular and highly rated music apps, has tipped Mavins records star, Ayra Starr for global recognition in 2022. The music app tipped the 20-year-old music star to rule the global music scene alongside Mexican American singer DannyLux, singer-songwriter Lyn Lapid, British music duo, Sad Night Dynamite, and K-pop girl group STAYC. According to a statement from Shazam, Ayra Starr’s rise in 2021 was largely mounted on her breakout track “Bloody Samaritan,” which had its first Shazam in Lagos.   Broda Shaggi promises to work harder in 2022     Toke Makinwa: Bloggers obsessed with my ‘private part’     I’m a gold digger, money can buy my love, says actress…   Read Also: What writing songs around Don Jazzy feels like – Ayra Starr The statement went further, “Bloody Samaritan was released as the lead single of the Nigerian singer-songwriter’s debut album 19 & Dangerous, but took on a life of its own as listeners were drawn in by an alluring violin melody that drops into contagious Afropop magic. An undeniable jam, “Bloody Samaritan” was the most Shazamed song by a local female artist in Nigeria in 2021.” - Advertisement - The music app owners further rated Ayra Starr’s run on Shazan as an impressive accomplishment considering the obvious fact that the single was released only in July.